DISCLAIMER: Not mine; HasTak's.
TITLE: "Repulsive"
SERIES/CONTINUITY: Transformers/G1 cartoon
RATING: PG.
PAIRING: N/A
WARNINGS: Thematic elements.
SUMMARY: Blitzwing's memories of the siege on Autobot City run away with him.  Inspired by the G1 prompt generator.

<lj-cut text="It was the sort of filth no amount of washing could rinse away."><hr>
Blitzwing didn't think he'd ever manage to fully wipe the memories from his databanks and he wasn't sure if that was more or less disgusting than how it felt when that old rustbucket of an Autobot grabbed him by the barrel.  He hated that he could still remember the weight as that green heap transformed and swung round, came down hard on his deck.  The sensation of hands that had no right to be that powerful at their age gripping him so tightly the metal crimped between knuckles was still fresh in his mind.  He continued to suffer occasional pains in his turret, bolts warped when his barrel was yanked out of alignment.

He couldn't really help thinking of what he'd do to that Autobot in revenge.  He knew it would feel good, too, serving up the same sort of indignity when he flipped that pitiful-looking old truck, grabbed him by the drive-shaft, and bent the thing back on itself.  He looked forward to finding out how much the oldtimer liked having the tables turned.

Then he shuddered in disgust and ran another purge.
</lj-cut>
